\section{General}

All executions of a skill are based on a difficulty Factor (DF) *
a Stat Basis (SB). There are a variety of mods that can be applied
to any skill.

\begin{table}[h]
\caption{DF Modifiers for Skill Based Actions}
\centering
	\begin{tabular}{||l|r||} \hline
	Condition                      &  Effect\\ \hline
	Suprise                        &  -1.0\\
	Unranked in Area               &  -2.0\\
	Setup(1)                       &  +1.0\\
	Adding 1st minor complexity(2) &  -0.5\\
	Adding 1st major complexity(3) &  -1.0 \\
	Adding 2nd minor complexity    &  -1.0\\
	Adding 2nd major complexity    &  -2.0 \\ \hline
	\end{tabular}
\end{table}

Setup should be done for as long as the event itself would take.

Minor complexities are typified by splitting perception during a 
physical action or moving while performing a mental action.

